List of changes (incomplete) 
============================


Up to 5 January 2015
--------------------

Changes
  - The aerial refueling status light logic is changed to closer
    reflect the rel ones on tankers
      - Amber when system is ready
      - Green when in contact
      - No lights whentanks are full
  - Replaced the cockpit clock with one more like the real one
    The main features are
      - Rotating minute bezel (kept in place between sessions)
      - Button below dial to start/stop/reset cronograph
      - Chronograph minute hand move in 1/2 minute steps


Up to 8 December 2014
---------------------

Additions
  - Aerial refueling status lights (fictional, due to *all* tankers
    missing their ones)
      - One amber ready/tanks full light
      - One green contact light
  - Warning horn sounds (not yet used)

Changes
  - Fuel remaining indicator is now in liters
  - Improved master failure warning light (not yet used)
  - Improved airbrake light

Bug fixes
  - Areal refueling is working again


Up to 8 November 2014
---------------------

Bug fixes
  - HUD is now only visible in pilot view (finally :-)

Changes
  - Mach and G now shows more decimals on the HUD
  - Air refueling contact radius changed from 5 to 25 meters


Up to 16 August 2014
--------------------

Additions
  - Air-to-air refueling (AAR) capability with a fuel transfer rate of
    1300 lbs/min based on NATO Doc ATP-56(B) dated November 2012, figures
    E3-1 and E4-1. Optimum altitude and CAS/Mach is stated to be
    FL250 and 305 kt/M 0.80.

Known issues
  - HUD visible in external views


Up to 31 May 2014
-----------------

Additions
  - Trim gauge

Bug fixes
  - Fixed problems with accented characters (i.e. removing the accents)

Known issues
  - HUD visible in external views
  - Air-to-air refueling does not work


Up to February 2014
-------------------

I migrated to from FlightGear 2.4.0 to 3.0.0 some time during February 2014.

Additions
  - A lot of instruments
      - Semi-functional lighting control panel
      - Configuration indicator
        (Shows position of gear, flaps, slats and use of wheel brakes)
      - Non-functional Autopilot control panel
      - Airbrake indicator light
      - Fuel remaining indicator (still in US gallons instead of liters)

Changes
  - Renamed the aircraft directory (if not earlier)
  - Added extra fuel tank to fix erroneous property
    /consumables/fuel/total-fuel-gal_us in order to make the fuel remaining
    indicator to work
  - Flap and slat settings to match reality

Known issues
  - HUD visible in external views
  - Air-to-air refueling does not work


Up to the end of 2012
---------------------

Additions
  - Slats section in the FDM

Changes
  - Slightly different stall parameters
  - Slightly different approach parameters

Known issues
  - HUD visible in external views
  - Air-to-air refueling does not work


Up to the end of 2011
---------------------

Additions
  - A HUD loosely based on a mix of unknown F1CR HUD modes
  - G tolerance
      - The pilot will handle +6/-2 G
      - Full Blackout/redout at +8/-4 G
  - Borrowed compass from the c172
  - Default field of view is now 90 degrees
  
Changes
  - Changed view point

Known issues
  - HUD visible in external views
  - Air-to-air refueling does not work


Fri 26 Aug 2011
---------------

First download of the original package
